          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1650380314071-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve <strong>half</strong> your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in a heatproof bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> couscous </strong>and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then stir, cover and set aside</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650380322036-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650380322036-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650380322036-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650380322036-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1650380322036-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>,<strong> remaining vegetable stock mix</strong>, your<strong> diced apricots</strong>,<strong> chopped tomatoes </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [175ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chickpeas have warmed through – this is your <strong>harissa</strong> <strong>chickpea & apricot tagine</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650380330450-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650380330450-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650380330450-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650380330450-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1650380330450-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tagine is cooking, add your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>tahini</strong></p><p>Add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>water</strong> to loosen and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>tahini yoghurt</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>cooked couscous </strong>with a fork</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1650380338639-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1650380338639-x400.jpg",
